title: Vote for The Bee’s Prep Football Player of the Week
text:
October 24, 2015 Vote for The Bee’s Prep Football Player of the Week Members of the Placer High School football team warm up before their game against Bear River on Friday October 23, 2015 in Grass Valley. Brian Baer sacbeephotos@sacbee.com i 
Who had the best performance of Week 8? 
Past weeks’ winners 
Tyler Stoever, Valley Christian: Returned an interception 51 yards for a touchdown and rushed for a score in a 34-12 win over Delta. 
Jayden Machado, Elk Grove: Passed for four touchdowns in a 63-14 win over Jesuit. 
Ryan Robards, Elk Grove: Scored touchdowns on an interception return, a fumble return, a punt return and three runs in a 42-7 win over Grant. 
Austin Weir, Colfax: Threw for 187 yards and four touchdowns in Colfax’s 42-7 win over Wheatland. 
Christian Huber, Folsom: Had six receptions for 150 yards and three touchdowns in Folsom’s 56-20 win over Burbank. 
Clarence Pierson, River Valley: Rushed for 220 yards and three touchdowns and had an interception in a 55-43 win over Roseville. 
Terrence March, Natomas: Rushed for 162 yards and two touchdowns, caught a 24-yard touchdown pass, scored on two two-point conversion runs and had 14 tackles and three sacks in a 42-24 victory over Valley. 
Michael Pittman, Oak Ridge: Rushed for 187 yards and scored five touchdowns in a 57-55 win over Whitney. Related content
